reviews.review_text:
Some questions Why include the NRPS set? On a good day they never rise above mediocre. In this case more is less.

Why was Pig's organ on Bertha replaced by the comparatively  flavorless Merl Saunders for the Skullfuck album? Pig's playing is much more interesting and rollicking. Treating Pig like that wasn't cool. Still a great album tho.

What's up with The Beach Boys stuff at the end? I guess they were on the bill? I like it though. Okie From Muscogee is hilarious. 

Otherwise the show's got that excellent mid-71 bar band on steroids sound. At times it can be a little loosey-goosey but the good far outweighs the slop, of course.
